Updated version from gg_2fort_compound. Many fixes, adjustments, and a few changes made. - Removed func_buyzone's from out of the map. In the oldschool gun game, there could be buyzones in the map without cause for problems, since the GG plug-in use to automatically disable buy-zones. Since recent updates of Gun Game, I have been told it no longer disables buy-zones. So this map is a fix. - Fixed many Prop Model Fade In / Out distances, to help up FPS and make the gameplay run smoother. - Added HDR Lighting to the map with a couple updated cube maps. - Changed Skybox background, adjusted env_light to match new sun, and preferred sdk brightness settings. - Added a couple smoke grenades in the map ( 8 Total ) 4 for CT, and 4 for T. Due to the fact that the map was actually designed around the usage of smoke grenades to push the field. - Replaced small old grandpa trees with bigger, greener and more lush trees. Adds a bit more cover and helps to balance the map size. - Updated lighting throughout the map and changed a couple light props. ...and a few other minor changes. To be honest, I wanted to add in a couple more rooms into the map, and interconnect the back room that leads to the sniper nest, (the hl2 marked door) with the front spawn room area. Also wanted to add in some more cover into the front field, though my main concern was to not change it up to much so that people didn't enjoy it anymore. Perhaps I will make another version soon, that is more expansive. Till then, ALL comments and suggestions are welcomed. gg_compound_hdr map by nintentofu

This map is a look-a-like to gg\_deagle\_assault, but we can't make a comparison between this maps. This is because my map has different boxes size (making paths with normal width and others thinner). Also, this map has breakable boxes. When we get to the map, there are standard paths to walk, which by themselves make a good gaming situation, but when we break the boxes, we add several more paths to the map, adding complexity and fun to the game. The paths are completely different from any other map. One other feature, I made 4 types of boxes (in texture ways), there are the unbreakable boxes and three different breakable boxes with different textures and resistance. I also made boxes of different sizes, and the boxes maintain the same resistance value (example, a box has 5 of resistance, half of that box has only 2.5 of resistance). To conclude, I also made some camping spots, which are very small, but that are placed so that players can humiliate others.


**Why name it gg\_200glockbullets?**

This was a random event. I was shooting all the breakable boxes (not spending a single bullet any other place and not making bullets pierce to the next box) and, at the end, I had spent 200 glock bullets breaking all those boxes! Of course I had to go buy another glock before I finished shooting them all. As I didn't had any idea for the map's name, I chose that one then xP


Well, I just hope you enjoy playing it as much I did ;)
Don't forget to comment and rate it :)
